# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat (new feature)
# * fix (bug fix)
# * docs (documentation)
# * style (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# * refactor (refactoring production code)
# * test (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
# * chore (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#
# Scope is optional and should be the name of the npm package affected
# (as perceived by person reading changelog generated from commit messages).
#
# Subject should use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# and don't capitalize first letter, and no dot (.) at the end.
#
# Body should include motivation for the change and contrast with previous behavior.
#
# Footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes and is also the place to
# reference GitHub issues that this commit Closes.